cmqttsnforwarder is a simple mqtt-sn forwarder that will forward mqtt-sn messages
                 from a client network over a gateway network to a mqtt-sn gateway.
version a1 is 0.1.0 (build date 28-06-2019 12:14:27).
Usage: cmqttsnforwarder {[[-h mqtt_sn_gateway_host] [-p mqtt_sn_gateway_port]] | -L URL}
                        [-gfp --gateway_find_pattern] [-awt --advertise_wait_timeout] [-sgr --search_gateway_radius]
                        [--gw_id_whitelist] [--gw_add_whitelist] [--gw_id_blacklist] [--gw_add_blacklist]
                        {[[-gP gateway_network_protocol] [-gA gateway_network_bind_address] [-gp gateway_network_bind_port]] | -gL URL}
                        {[[-gbP gateway_network_broadcast_protocol] [-gbA gateway_network_broadcast_address] [-gbp gateway_network_broadcast_bind_port]] | -gbL URL}
                        {[[-gst gateway_send_timeout] [-grt gateway_receive_timeout]] | --gt gateway_network_timeout}
                        [-gnp gateway_network_plugin]
                        {[[-cP client_network_protocol] [-cA client_network_bind_address] [-cp client_network_bind_port]] | -cL URL}
                        {[[-cst client_send_timeout] [-crt client_receive_timeout]] | --ct client_network_timeout}
                        {[[-cbP client_network_broadcast_protocol] [-cbA client_network_broadcast_address] [-cbp client_network_broadcast_bind_port]] | -cbL URL}
                        [-cnp client_network_plugin]
                        [[-q quiet] | [-d default] | [-v verbose] | [-db debug]]


 -h : mqtt-sn gateway host to connect to. Defaults to localhost.
 -p : mqtt-sn gateway network port to connect to. Defaults to 8888 for plain MQTT-SN.
 -L : specify hostname, port as a URL in the form:
      mqttsn(s)://host[:port]
      mqttsn(s) uses the same protocol as the gateway network.
 -gfp : specify the mqtt-sn gateway find pattern.
        Can be any, advertise, search, connect. Default is any.
 -awt : specify advertise wait timeout in s. Default is 60 s.
 -sgt : specify SearchGw timeout in s. Default is 60 s.
 -sgr : specify radius of SearchGw message between 0 and 255. Default is 1.
 --gw_id_whitelist : specify whitelist for mqtt-sn gateway ids. Can be used repeatedly. Maximum entry count is 5.
 --gw_add_whitelist : specify whitelist for mqtt-sn gateway addresses. Can be used repeatedly. Maximum entry count is 5.
 --gw_id_blacklist : specify blaclist for mqtt-sn gateway ids. Can be used repeatedly. Maximum entry count is 5.
 --gw_add_blacklist : specify blacklist for mqtt-sn gateway addresses. Can be used repeatedly. Maximum entry count is 5.
 -gP : specify the protocol of the gateway network to use.
       Can be udp, tcp. Defaults to udp.
 -gA : bind the gateway network to the outgoing socket to this host/ip address.
       Use to control which interface to communicates over or to set the address for the gateway network.
 -gp : listening on the specific gateway network port. Defaults to 9999.
       A port overwrites the two last bytes of the gateway network bind address. You can set gateway port to -1 if you want to overwrite this behaviour
 -gL : specify protocol, address, port as a URL in the form: protocol://address[:port]
 -gbP : specify the protocol of the gateway network broadcast to use.
        Can be udp. Defaults to udp.
 -gbA : specify the gateway network broadcast address.
        Note: the gateway network broadcast binds to the gateway network bind interface.
        Defaults to 224.1.1.100.
 -gbp : listening on the specific gateway network broadcast port. Defaults to 5353.
 -gbL : specify protocol, address, port as a URL in the form: protocol://address[:port]
 -gst : specify the gateway network send timeout in ms.
       on 0 returns immediately, on -1 waits indefinitely for a message. Defaults to 1000 ms.
 -grt : specify the gateway network receive timeout in ms.
       on 0 returns immediately, on -1 waits indefinitely for a message. Defaults to 1000 ms.
 -gt  : specify the gateway network send and receive timeout in ms.
       on 0 returns immediately, on -1 waits indefinitely for a message.
 -gnp : path to the gateway network plugin.
       The gateway network protocol must match the short protocol name gained from the plugin.
       A gateway bind address is saved to a device address and given to the gateway network plugin.
       A port overwrites the two last bytes of the gateway network bind address. You can set gateway port to -1 if you want to overwrite this behaviour
 -cP : specify the protocol of the client network to use.
       Can be udp, tcp. Defaults to udp.
 -cp : listening on the specific client network port. Defaults to 8888.
 -cL : specify protocol, broadcast address, port as a URL in the form: protocol://address[:port]
 -cst : specify the client network send timeout in ms.
        On 0 returns immediately, on -1 waits indefinitely for a message. Defaults to 1000 ms.
 -crt : specify the client network receive timeout in ms.
        On 0 returns immediately, on -1 waits indefinitely for a message. Defaults to 1000 ms.
 -ct  : specify the client network send and receive timeout in ms.
 -cbP : specify the protocol of the client network broadcast to use.
        Can be udp. Defaults to udp.
 -cbA : specify the client network broadcast address. Defaults to 224.1.1.101.
        Note: the client network broadcast binds to the client network bind interface.
 -cbp : listening on the specific client network broadcast port. Defaults to 5352.
 -cbL : specify protocol, address, port as a URL in the form: protocol://address[:port]
 -cnp : absolute path to the client network plugin.
        The client network protocol must match the short protocol name gained from the plugin.
        A client bind address is saved to a device address and given to the gateway network plugin.
        A client port overwrites the two last bytes of the gateway network bind address.
        You can set client port to -1 if you want to overwrite this behaviour.
 -q : specify quiet logging. Don't print any log messages.
 -d : specify default logging. Enables default log messages.
 -v : specify verbose logging. Enables verbose log messages.
 -db : specify debug logging. Enables debug log messages.